 near a tower, usually a defensive fortification or watchtower, from Middle English, Old French <i>tūr</i> (from Latin <i>turris</i>).","English: occupational name for someone who dressed white leather, cured with alum rather than tanned with bark, from an agent derivative of Middle English <i>taw(en)</i> (Old English <i>tawian</i> ‘to prepare, make ready’).","Americanized form of German   Tauer  ."]}]},{"name":"Thomas","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament name, borne by one of Christ's twelve apostles, referred to as ‘Thomas, called Didymus’ (John 11:16; 20:24). <i>Didymos</i> is the Greek word for ‘twin’, and the name is the Greek form of an Aramaic byname meaning ‘twin’. The given name has always been popular throughout Christendom, in part because St Thomas's doubts have made him seem a very human character."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705191,"age":5,"year":"1315","toYear":"1317","julianDay":2201354,"title":"Famine Strikes Europe","description":"A famine caused by cold winters and wet summers across Europe caused millions to die due to starvation. Desperation from hunger caused high levels of crime, stampedes in bread lines in London, infanticide, and even cannibalism throughout Europe.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705192,"age":18,"year":"1328","julianDay":2206102,"title":"First War of Scottish Independence","description":"The First War of Scottish Independence began after England invaded Scotland in 1296. The Treaty of Edinburgh was signed in 1328 which declared peace between the two kingdoms and brought the war to an end.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705195,"age":72,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Thomas Towers was born in 1310, in Somerby, Lincolnshire, England, his father, Thomas Tower, was 20 and his mother, Mrs. Thomas Tower, was 21. He had at least 2 sons with Joan Staveley."},"et":{"1310–":"1310–Surnud","1310–Male":"1310–Surnud","1315–Female":"1315–Surnud","1330–Male":"1330–Surnud","1362–Male":"1362–Surnud","1290–Male":"1290–Surnud","1290–Female":"1290–Surnud","1315":"1315","1310":"1310","1330":"1330","1362":"1362","abt 1362":"umbes 1362","1382":"1382","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","1290":"1290","Somerby, Lincolnshire, England":"Somerby, Lincolnshire, England","Somerby, Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom":"Somerby, Lincolnshire, England","Thornock, Lincs, Eng":"Lincolnshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1310–":"1310–Kuollut","1310–Male":"1310–Kuollut","1315–Female":"1315–Kuollut","1330–Male":"1330–Kuollut","1362–Male":"1362–Kuollut","1290–Male":"1290–Kuollut","1290–Female":"1290–Kuollut","1315":"1315","1310":"1310","1330":"1330","1362":"1362","abt 1362":"noin 1362","1382":"1382","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","1290":"1290","Somerby, Lincolnshire, England":"Somerby, Lincolnshire, England","Somerby, Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom":"Somerby, Lincolnshire, England","Thornock, Lincs, Eng":"Lincolnshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1310–":"1310–Décédé","1310–Male":"1310–Décédé","1315–Female":"1315–Décédée","1330–Male":"1330–Décédé","1362–Male":"1362–Décédé","1290–Male":"1290–Décédé","1290–Female":"1290–Décédée","1315":"1315","1310":"1310","1330":"1330","1362":"1362","abt 1362":"environ 1362","1382":"1382","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","1290":"1290","Somerby, Lincolnshire, England":"Somerby, Lincolnshire, Angleterre","Somerby, Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom":"Somerby, Lincolnshire, Angleterre","Thornock, Lincs, Eng":"Lincolnshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lif